    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A novelist is working on a new book and wants to find examples of words they can use for a specific part of speech. They are using a small sample of data to practice working with strings.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** Write the method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getWordsForPart()</code> in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Novel</code> class. This method should:\r\n\r\n- Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">indexOf()</code> and <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">substring()</code> to find the list of words for a fixed part of speech.\r\n- Only work for the input <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"noun\"</code>.\r\n- Extract and return the word list for nouns in the format: \r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #333; color: white;\">dog\r\ncat</pre>\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">NovelRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getWordsForPart()</code> method and print the result.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> The format of the data string is: <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"noun:dog,cat\\nverb:run,jump\\nadjective:blue,quick\"</code>\r\n</div>\r\n",
